<worksheet label="ws-act-8-2-1">
  <page>
    <activity xml:id="act-8-2-1" workspace="3cm">
      <introduction>
        <p>
      Let <m>a</m> and <m>r</m> be real numbers
      (with <m>r \ne 1</m>)
      and let
      <me>
        S_n = a+ar+ar^2 + \cdots + ar^{n-1}
      </me>.
    </p>
        <p>
      In this activity we will find a shortcut formula for <m>S_n</m> that does not involve a sum of <m>n</m> terms.
    </p>
        <p/>
      </introduction>
      <task workspace="3cm" xml:id="act-8-2-1-task-0">
        <statement>
          <p>
            Multiply <m>S_n</m> by <m>r</m>.
            What does the resulting sum look like?
          </p>
        </statement>
        <hint>
          <p>
            Distribute the factor of <m>r</m>.
          </p>
        </hint>
        <answer>
          <p><m> rS_n = ar+ar^2+ar^3 + \cdots + ar^n </m>.
          </p>
        </answer>
        <solution>
          <p>
            Note that
            <me>
              rS_n = ar+ar^2+ar^3 + \cdots + ar^n
            </me>.
          </p>
        </solution>
      </task>
      <task workspace="3cm" xml:id="act-8-2-1-task-1">
        <statement>
          <p>
            Subtract <m>rS_n</m> from <m>S_n</m> and explain why
            <men xml:id="eq-8-2-1-partial-geometric-sum">
              S_n - rS_n = a - ar^n
            </men>.
          </p>
        </statement>
        <hint>
          <p>
            Look for common terms in the two expressions being subtracted.
          </p>
        </hint>
        <answer>
          <p><m>S_n - rS_n = a - ar^n</m>.
          </p>
        </answer>
        <solution>
          <p>
            When we subtract <m>rS_n</m> from <m>S_n</m> the middle terms all cancel and we are left with
            <md><mrow>S_n - rS_n \amp = \left(a+ar+ar^2 + \cdots + ar^{n-1}\right)</mrow><mrow>\amp\phantom{={}}{}- \left(ar+ar^2+ar^3 + \cdots + ar^n\right)</mrow><mrow>\amp =a + (ar-ar) + \left(ar^2-ar^2\right) + \cdots + \left(ar^{n-1}-ar^{n-1}\right) - ar^n</mrow><mrow>\amp = a - ar^n</mrow></md>.
          </p>
        </solution>
      </task>
      <task workspace="3cm" xml:id="act-8-2-1-task-2">
        <statement>
          <p>
            Solve equation <xref ref="eq-8-2-1-partial-geometric-sum"/> for <m>S_n</m> to find a simple formula for <m>S_n</m> that does not involve adding <m>n</m> terms.
          </p>
        </statement>
        <hint>
          <p>
            Observe that you can remove a factor of <m>S_n</m> from <m>S_n - rS_n</m>.
          </p>
        </hint>
        <answer>
          <p><m>S_n = a\frac{1-r^n}{1-r}</m>.
          </p>
        </answer>
        <solution>
          <p>
            Factoring <m>S_n</m> from left hand side and dividing gives us a formula for <m>S_n</m>:
            <md><mrow>S_n(1-r) \amp = a - ar^n</mrow><mrow>S_n \amp = a\frac{1-r^n}{1-r}</mrow></md>.
          </p>
        </solution>
      </task>
    </activity>
  </page>
</worksheet>
